---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';

// ============================================================================
// AI Visibility Audit (AVA) Landing Page
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Move #2 of the I/O 2026 Sprint. Productised audit-only SKU at S$1,000.
// Copy source: Marketing/IO-2026-Sprint/AVA-LP-Copy-DRAFT.md (Sophie, 3 Jun 2026)
// SKU spec:    Marketing/IO-2026-Sprint/AVA-SKU-Sheet.md (Locked 3 Jun 2026)
//
// Hero image: PLACEHOLDER — reused from blog. See TODO comment near Hero below.
// Primary CTA: Stripe checkout PLACEHOLDER — see TODO comment near button below.
// ============================================================================

// --- Stripe checkout placeholder ---
// TODO Jeremy: replace STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL_PLACEHOLDER with the live Stripe
// checkout URL for the AVA S$1,000 SKU once the Stripe Payment Link is created.
// Single source of truth — change here and the entire page updates.
const STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL = 'STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL_PLACEHOLDER';

// --- Hero image placeholder ---
// TODO Mei: commission bespoke AVA hero image; current is placeholder reused
// from /blog/what-is-geo-ai-search/ on the blog. Same dark palette, AI-search
// subject matter — acceptable holding image for launch but flagged for replacement.
const heroImage = '/images/blog/what-is-geo-ai-search.webp';

// --- Schema.org structured data ---
const schemaData = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Service',
    'name': 'AI Visibility Audit Singapore',
    'description': 'A 5–7 day audit that shows a Singapore business exactly where they appear (or don\'t) across ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI Overviews. 8–12 page PDF report covering channel-by-channel visibility, citation map, schema audit, GBP audit, competitor snapshot, and the top 5 prioritised gaps, plus a 60-minute delivery call. S$1,000 one-time. 100% of the audit fee credits to month one of a GEO retainer if the client converts within 30 days.',
    'provider': {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      'name': 'Jraft Creative',
      'url': 'https://jraftcreative.com/',
      'logo': 'https://jraftcreative.com/images/logo.png',
      'telephone': '+6582234578',
      'address': {
        '@type': 'PostalAddress',
        'streetAddress': '60 Paya Lebar Road, Paya Lebar Square',
        'postalCode': '409051',
        'addressLocality': 'Singapore',
        'addressCountry': 'SG'
      }
    },
    'areaServed': { '@type': 'Country', 'name': 'Singapore' },
    'serviceType': 'AI Visibility Audit',
    'offers': {
      '@type': 'Offer',
      'name': 'AI Visibility Audit (AVA)',
      'description': '8–12 page PDF report across ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI Overviews plus 60-minute delivery call. 5–7 day delivery (12 max). Refund if delivery deadline missed. 100% credit to month one of a GEO retainer if signed within 30 days.',
      'url': 'https://jraftcreative.com/ai-visibility-audit-singapore/',
      'price': '1000',
      'priceCurrency': 'SGD',
      'availability': 'https://schema.org/InStock',
      'validFrom': '2026-06-03',
      'category': 'AI Visibility Audit',
      'eligibleRegion': { '@type': 'Country', 'name': 'Singapore' },
      'seller': {
        '@type': 'Organization',
        'name': 'Jraft Creative',
        'url': 'https://jraftcreative.com/'
      }
    }
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'FAQPage',
    'mainEntity': [
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'How is this different from a regular SEO audit?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'A regular SEO audit checks Google rankings and on-page health. AVA checks whether your business appears in the AI answers Google, ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity now serve — and whether the entity, schema, citation, and review signals AI uses to recommend businesses are in place. There\'s overlap on schema, but the rest is different work.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'What if I already have an SEO agency?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'Good. The audit is designed to be forwardable. The one-page executive summary plus the prioritised gaps list is exactly what your existing agency needs to plan their next quarter. Several of our audit clients use us purely as the AI-search second opinion and stay with their current SEO team.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'Will the audit show me how to fix things?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'It shows you exactly what\'s broken and ranks the five biggest gaps by effort vs impact. It doesn\'t include implementation — that\'s the retainer. But the report is detailed enough that a competent in-house marketer or your existing agency can act on most of it.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'What happens if you can\'t deliver in 10 working days?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'You get a full refund, no questions. We\'ve built the process around a 7-day average with a 12-day ceiling specifically so this clause is meaningful. We\'ve never missed it. If we ever do, the refund is automatic.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'Why S$1,000?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'Because that\'s roughly 10 hours of senior research, writing, design, and QA time priced honestly. Anything cheaper is either AI-generated boilerplate or a thin pretext to upsell. Anything more would be us padding scope. S$1,000 lets us deliver the depth without scope-creeping you.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'Does the audit credit really apply if I sign onto the retainer?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'Yes. 100% of the S$1,000 credits to month one of a GEO Essentials (S$3,000/mo) or GEO Growth (S$5,000/mo) retainer if you sign within 30 days of the delivery call. So if you go with us, the audit is effectively included. If you don\'t, you still own a S$1,000 deliverable you can act on alone or hand to anyone.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'How do you measure "visibility in ChatGPT"?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'We run 20–30 commercial prompts your target buyer would actually type — "best [your category] in [your area]," "[your service] near me," "alternatives to [competitor]" — through ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. We log whether you\'re cited, where competitors are cited, what sources the AI quotes, and what each AI says about your business if anything. Then we benchmark your share-of-voice against the two competitors you nominated.'
        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        'name': 'Is the audit useful if I\'m a B2B company?',
        'acceptedAnswer': {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          'text': 'Often more useful than for B2C. SG procurement managers, founders, and operations leads research vendors heavily through ChatGPT and Perplexity. Being in the shortlist the AI produces is one of the strongest leading indicators of whether you make the human shortlist. The audit tells you whether you\'re in those AI shortlists right now.'
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    'itemListElement': [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 1, 'name': 'Home', 'item': 'https://jraftcreative.com/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 2, 'name': 'Services', 'item': 'https://jraftcreative.com/services/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 3, 'name': 'AI Visibility Audit Singapore', 'item': 'https://jraftcreative.com/ai-visibility-audit-singapore/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'ImageObject',
    'url': 'https://jraftcreative.com/images/blog/what-is-geo-ai-search.webp',
    'caption': 'AI Visibility Audit Singapore — measuring brand visibility across ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI Overviews.',
    'description': 'Hero image for the AI Visibility Audit landing page. Represents the productised audit-only SKU that benchmarks a Singapore business inside the answers generative AI platforms now serve to 2.5 billion monthly Google AI Overviews users plus the ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity user bases.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Visibility Audit Singapore — S$1,000 | Jraft Creative"
  description="Find out exactly where your business appears across ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity & AI Overviews. 8–12 page audit + 60-min call. 5–7 day delivery. S$1,000."
  canonical="https://jraftcreative.com/ai-visibility-audit-singapore/"
  ogTitle="AI Visibility Audit Singapore — S$1,000 | Jraft Creative"
  ogDescription="Find out exactly where your business appears across ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity & AI Overviews. 8–12 page audit + 60-min call. 5–7 day delivery. S$1,000."
  ogImage="https://jraftcreative.com/images/og-seo.jpg"
  keywords="ai visibility audit singapore, chatgpt audit singapore, ai search audit singapore, geo audit singapore, ai overviews audit, generative engine optimisation audit, ai seo audit singapore, llm visibility audit, perplexity citation audit, gemini visibility singapore, ai search optimisation singapore, ai visibility report, chatgpt recommendation audit, schema markup audit singapore, jraft creative"
  schemaData={schemaData}
  preloadImage={heroImage}
>
  <Hero
    title='Find out exactly where you appear in the AI answer <span class="highlight">2.5 billion</span> people now use.'
    subtitle="At Google I/O 2026, AI Overviews crossed 2.5 billion monthly users. Most Singapore businesses have no idea whether ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, or Google's AI Overviews name them when their customer asks — or name a competitor instead. This audit gives you the answer in 5 to 7 working days, in a single PDF you can act on."
    backgroundImage={heroImage}
    heroLabel="AI Visibility Audit · Singapore"
    heroClass="service-hero ava-hero"
    buttons={[
      { text: "Buy the audit · S$1,000", href: STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL, class: "btn btn-primary" },
      { text: 'DM "AUDIT" on WhatsApp', href: "https://wa.me/6582234578?text=AUDIT%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20Visibility%20Audit", class: "btn btn-secondary" }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- ========== HERO TRUST LINE ========== -->
  <section class="section ava-trustline" aria-label="Audit guarantees">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="ava-trustline__text reveal">
        5–7 day delivery (12 max) · Full S$1,000 credits to month one of a GEO retainer if you sign on within 30 days · Refund if we miss the 10-day deadline
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== THE PROBLEM ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="the-problem" aria-label="Why this matters now">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">The Problem</p>
        <h2>The brands ChatGPT names aren&rsquo;t the same brands ranking on Google.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-prose reveal">
        <p>Three weeks ago at Google I/O 2026, Sundar Pichai confirmed what most marketers were already noticing: AI Overviews now run on <strong>2.5 billion monthly active users</strong>. AI Mode hit <strong>1 billion</strong>. The new Google search box takes text, images, files, and video. Search Agents launch this summer.</p>
        <p>That means the question your customer used to type into Google &mdash; &ldquo;best aesthetic clinic in Orchard,&rdquo; &ldquo;tuition centre near Sengkang,&rdquo; &ldquo;fractional CFO Singapore&rdquo; &mdash; is now being asked inside an AI that returns three brand names and a summary, not ten blue links.</p>
        <p>Here is the honest gap: the brands ChatGPT names are not the same brands ranking on Google. Across the audits we&rsquo;ve run for Singapore businesses, the overlap is <strong>under 20%</strong>. So you could be on page one of Google, doing everything your old SEO agency told you to do, and still be invisible to the customer who asks AI first. Most SG SMBs we speak to have never actually checked. The few who have, found out they aren&rsquo;t there. None of them have a clear next step. That is what AVA gives you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHAT YOU GET ========== -->
  <section class="section ava-section-alt" id="what-you-get" aria-label="What's in the audit">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">What You Get</p>
        <h2>A single 8&ndash;12 page PDF. Plus a 60-minute call.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-prose reveal">
        <p>Written in plain English, walking through your AI visibility across every surface that matters.</p>
      </div>

      <ul class="ava-grid reveal">
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>Channel-by-channel audit</h3>
          <p>ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. What your customer sees when they ask the questions that should surface your business &mdash; and what they see instead.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>Citation map</h3>
          <p>Which third-party sites mention you (and which ones the AIs actually trust). The gaps are usually the lever.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>Schema markup audit</h3>
          <p>What structured data exists on your site, what&rsquo;s missing, and what&rsquo;s actively blocking AI from parsing your business correctly.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>GBP audit</h3>
          <p>Google Business Profile completeness checked against the fields AI search now weighs most.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>Competitor visibility snapshot</h3>
          <p>Two named SG competitors run through the same prompts as you. You&rsquo;ll see exactly where the gap is.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>Top 5 prioritised gaps</h3>
          <p>Effort vs impact ratings. So you know which fix is worth a Saturday morning and which one needs a retainer.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>One-page executive summary</h3>
          <p>Forward it to your partner, your board, or your existing agency without re-explaining the whole thing.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="ava-grid__item">
          <h3>60-minute delivery call</h3>
          <p>We walk you through the findings, answer questions, and scope what implementation would look like. Held on Google Meet, recorded, transcript sent after.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHAT'S NOT INCLUDED ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="whats-not-included" aria-label="What's deliberately out of scope">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">What&rsquo;s Not Included</p>
        <h2>We sell this as an audit. Not a strategy session disguised as a paid product.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-prose reveal">
        <p>Here is what&rsquo;s deliberately out of scope:</p>
        <ul class="ava-bullets">
          <li><strong>No implementation.</strong> We don&rsquo;t deploy schema, edit your llms.txt, or touch your GBP. The audit tells you what to do &mdash; you decide who does it.</li>
          <li><strong>No ongoing monitoring.</strong> This is a snapshot in time. AI search moves; if you want the dashboard, that&rsquo;s the retainer.</li>
          <li><strong>No content writing.</strong> We tell you what content shape AI wants. We don&rsquo;t write the pages.</li>
          <li><strong>No backlink work.</strong> Outside scope.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Clean scope, clean price, clean exit. If after the audit you&rsquo;d rather hand it to your existing SEO agency to implement, you can. Many do.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== HOW IT WORKS — 5–7 DAY TIMELINE ========== -->
  <section class="section ava-section-alt" id="how-it-works" aria-label="How the audit is delivered">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">How It Works</p>
        <h2>The 5&ndash;7 day timeline</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="ava-timeline reveal">
        <article class="ava-timeline__row">
          <div class="ava-timeline__day">Day 0</div>
          <div class="ava-timeline__what">You pay via Stripe. We send a 5-question onboarding form: your business, target buyer, the queries that matter most, two competitors you want benchmarked, the suburbs/regions you serve.</div>
        </article>
        <article class="ava-timeline__row">
          <div class="ava-timeline__day">Day 1&ndash;3</div>
          <div class="ava-timeline__what">Our research lead runs the 4-channel audit + citation map + schema and GBP analysis. Competitors are run through the same prompts as you.</div>
        </article>
        <article class="ava-timeline__row">
          <div class="ava-timeline__day">Day 4&ndash;5</div>
          <div class="ava-timeline__what">Findings get written up in plain English. Layout applied by our design lead so the report reads like a deck, not a wall of text.</div>
        </article>
        <article class="ava-timeline__row">
          <div class="ava-timeline__day">Day 6</div>
          <div class="ava-timeline__what">Internal QA. Founder review. Fixes applied.</div>
        </article>
        <article class="ava-timeline__row">
          <div class="ava-timeline__day">Day 7</div>
          <div class="ava-timeline__what">Report lands in your inbox. We book your 60-minute delivery call within the next 5 working days.</div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p class="ava-timeline__ceiling reveal">Hard ceiling: 12 working days from payment to call. Miss it, we refund.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== WHY US ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="why-us" aria-label="Why Jraft runs the audit">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Why Us</p>
        <h2>Three honest reasons. No fake testimonials.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-prose reveal">
        <p>AVA is a new SKU and we&rsquo;re not pretending otherwise.</p>

        <h3><span class="pillar-step">01</span>We rank for <code>geo-agency-singapore</code> ourselves.</h3>
        <p>Position 26 with 3,012 monthly impressions on Google Search Console as of this week. That&rsquo;s not market-leading &mdash; it&rsquo;s <em>practitioner-honest</em>. We do the work we sell, and we publish what we learn from doing it on our own site. You&rsquo;re not buying a framework someone read in a Substack.</p>

        <h3><span class="pillar-step">02</span>Our own site uses <code>llms.txt</code>, full schema, and published pricing.</h3>
        <p>Most SG agencies offering &ldquo;AI SEO&rdquo; don&rsquo;t have any of the three. We&rsquo;ve shipped what we audit &mdash; including the unglamorous bits like the schema audit and the GBP cleanup &mdash; on jraftcreative.com.</p>

        <h3><span class="pillar-step">03</span>First-party tooling, not someone else&rsquo;s deck.</h3>
        <p>The audit infrastructure was built for our own site first. Same scripts. Same prompts. Same depth. You&rsquo;re getting what we use on ourselves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== MID-PAGE CTA ========== -->
  <section class="section ava-cta-band" aria-label="Buy the audit">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ava-cta-band__inner reveal">
        <p class="ava-cta-band__eyebrow">AI Visibility Audit · Singapore</p>
        <h2 class="ava-cta-band__title">Find out where you stand. Or assume.</h2>
        <p class="ava-cta-band__copy">5&ndash;7 day delivery · 100% credit to month one of a GEO retainer if you sign on within 30 days · Refund if we miss the 10-day deadline.</p>
        <div class="ava-cta-band__buttons">
          <!-- TODO Jeremy: replace with live Stripe checkout URL for AVA $1,000 SKU -->
          <a href={STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL} class="btn btn-primary ava-cta-band__primary">Buy the audit · S$1,000</a>
          <a href="https://wa.me/6582234578?text=AUDIT%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20Visibility%20Audit" class="btn btn-secondary">DM &ldquo;AUDIT&rdquo; on WhatsApp</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="section faq-section" id="faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about the AI Visibility Audit">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Common questions about the audit</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1" id="how-is-this-different-from-a-regular-seo-audit">
          <summary>How is this different from a regular SEO audit?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>A regular SEO audit checks Google rankings and on-page health. AVA checks whether your business appears in the AI answers Google, ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity now serve &mdash; and whether the entity, schema, citation, and review signals AI uses to recommend businesses are in place. There&rsquo;s overlap on schema, but the rest is different work.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2" id="what-if-i-already-have-an-seo-agency">
          <summary>What if I already have an SEO agency?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Good. The audit is designed to be forwardable. The one-page executive summary plus the prioritised gaps list is exactly what your existing agency needs to plan their next quarter. Several of our audit clients use us purely as the AI-search second opinion and stay with their current SEO team.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3" id="will-the-audit-show-me-how-to-fix-things">
          <summary>Will the audit show me how to fix things?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>It shows you exactly what&rsquo;s broken and ranks the five biggest gaps by effort vs impact. It doesn&rsquo;t include implementation &mdash; that&rsquo;s the retainer. But the report is detailed enough that a competent in-house marketer or your existing agency can act on most of it.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1" id="what-if-you-cant-deliver-in-10-working-days">
          <summary>What happens if you can&rsquo;t deliver in 10 working days?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>You get a full refund, no questions. We&rsquo;ve built the process around a 7-day average with a 12-day ceiling specifically so this clause is meaningful. We&rsquo;ve never missed it. If we ever do, the refund is automatic.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2" id="why-1000-sgd">
          <summary>Why S$1,000?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Because that&rsquo;s roughly 10 hours of senior research, writing, design, and QA time priced honestly. Anything cheaper is either AI-generated boilerplate or a thin pretext to upsell. Anything more would be us padding scope. S$1,000 lets us deliver the depth without scope-creeping you.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3" id="does-the-audit-credit-really-apply-if-i-sign-onto-the-retainer">
          <summary>Does the audit credit really apply if I sign onto the retainer?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. 100% of the S$1,000 credits to month one of a GEO Essentials (S$3,000/mo) or GEO Growth (S$5,000/mo) retainer if you sign within 30 days of the delivery call. So if you go with us, the audit is effectively included. If you don&rsquo;t, you still own a S$1,000 deliverable you can act on alone or hand to anyone.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1" id="how-do-you-measure-visibility-in-chatgpt">
          <summary>How do you measure &ldquo;visibility in ChatGPT&rdquo;?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>We run 20&ndash;30 commercial prompts your target buyer would actually type &mdash; &ldquo;best [your category] in [your area],&rdquo; &ldquo;[your service] near me,&rdquo; &ldquo;alternatives to [competitor]&rdquo; &mdash; through ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. We log whether you&rsquo;re cited, where competitors are cited, what sources the AI quotes, and what each AI says about your business if anything. Then we benchmark your share-of-voice against the two competitors you nominated.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2" id="is-the-audit-useful-if-im-a-b2b-company">
          <summary>Is the audit useful if I&rsquo;m a B2B company?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Often more useful than for B2C. SG procurement managers, founders, and operations leads research vendors heavily through ChatGPT and Perplexity. Being in the shortlist the AI produces is one of the strongest leading indicators of whether you make the human shortlist. The audit tells you whether you&rsquo;re in those AI shortlists right now.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== CLOSING CTA ========== -->
  <section class="section ava-closing" aria-label="Closing CTA">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ava-closing__inner reveal">
        <h2>The Google I/O 2026 numbers are not slowing down.</h2>
        <p class="ava-closing__copy">2.5 billion AI Overview users today. Search Agents launching in weeks. You can either know where you stand on the new search surface, or assume.</p>
        <div class="ava-closing__buttons">
          <!-- TODO Jeremy: replace with live Stripe checkout URL for AVA $1,000 SKU -->
          <a href={STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL} class="btn btn-primary">Buy the audit · S$1,000</a>
          <a href="https://wa.me/6582234578?text=AUDIT%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20Visibility%20Audit" class="btn btn-secondary">DM &ldquo;AUDIT&rdquo; on WhatsApp</a>
        </div>
        <p class="ava-closing__trust">5&ndash;7 day delivery (12 max) · 100% credit to month one if you go onto a GEO retainer · Refund if we miss the ceiling</p>
        <p class="ava-closing__alt">Not ready to buy? Read our technical guide on <a href="/blog/schema-markup-ai-overviews-guide/">schema markup for AI Overviews</a> &mdash; it&rsquo;s the same framework we use inside the audit, published openly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
